messages.message:
I used the SDK for the first time today, worked really well :fire:

There is a small issue either with the docs or the implementation. In the docs here (https://platform.instabase.com/docs/aihub/apis/apps-api/index.html#complete-workflow), it says get set the `owner=None` if its yours. When I do that i get an error, when I don’t set the owner to anything at all it works fine
Also doesn’t work if you provide another username
Thanks for reporting. Will fix it by EOD and make a new release.

Adding missing fields for a few APIs and published 0.1.3.
Do
```pip install --upgrade instabase-aihub ```
